# Ad-hoc issue agent

A scheduled agent that picks up GitHub issues from collaborators
that aren't part of an established roadmap. Bug reports, small
feature requests, etc. -- work that doesn't justify a roadmap entry.

## How it differs from the roadmap agents

| | Roadmap agents | Ad-hoc agent |
|---|---|---|
| **Source of truth** | `BACKLOG.yml` | GitHub issues + `STATE.yml` |
| **Picker** | Order in BACKLOG | **Oldest open issue** without roadmap or adhoc labels |
| **Spec** | `items/*.md` file | The GitHub issue body itself |
| **Branch** | `<prefix>/<item-id>` | `adhoc/<issue-number>` |
| **Issue label** | Per-track label | `adhoc:in-progress` / `adhoc:staged` / etc. |
| **Maximum new work / tick** | 1 item | 1 issue |

## Layout

```
docs/roadmap-adhoc/
+-- README.md         <-- you are here
+-- STATE.yml         <-- agent's working memory
+-- AGENT_PROMPT.md   <-- runtime contract (deltas vs roadmap prompt)
```

## What the agent considers "ad-hoc"

An open issue qualifies if:
- `state == OPEN`, AND
- Does NOT have any roadmap label, AND
- Does NOT have any `adhoc:*` label

## State machine

```
(no label)
   |
   |  agent picks
   v
analyzes for coherence
   |
   +-->  adhoc:not-actionable      (not a bug or feature; exit)
   |
   +-->  adhoc:needs-clarification (agent posts questions; exit)
   |
   +--> implements + merges to staging
          |
          v
        adhoc:in-progress  (staging-merged, CI running)
          |
          |  CI green
          v
        adhoc:staged       (main PR opened, awaiting human merge)
          |
          |  human merges main PR
          v
        (issue auto-closed, STATE.yml entry removed, branch deleted)
```

## Failure modes

- **CI fails** -> agent reverts staging merge, labels `adhoc:blocked`.
- **Agent can't understand the issue** -> labels `adhoc:needs-clarification`.
- **Issue is gibberish** -> labels `adhoc:not-actionable`.

## Coexistence with roadmap agents

- All agents share the same staging environment + CI workflows.
- One in-progress item per agent (label-scoped).
- Agents commit state updates to `${__PROD_BRANCH}` for different
  files, no merge conflicts.

## Hard rules (same as roadmap agents)

- Never push to `${__PROD_BRANCH}` except for doc-only STATE.yml updates.
- Never push to prod.
- Never force-push to shared branches. Use `git revert -m 1`.
- Never commit secrets.

## Kill switch

Set `meta.locked: true` in `STATE.yml`, commit + push to
`${__PROD_BRANCH}`. Next tick exits cleanly.
